From the manufacturer

Honeywell TH8320R1003 VisionPro 8000 with RedLINK Digital Thermostat, White

Product Features
  • Color: White
  • Seven-day programming
  • Touch-screen interaction
  • Large, easy-to-read backlit display
  • Dual-powered battery or hard-wired
  • Residential or commercial use
  • ENERGY STAR certified
  • Professional installation

VisionPro 8000 with RedLINK Digital Thermostat

VisionPRO 8000 with RedLINK Thermostat functions like a mobile device with a touch screen and menu-driven programming.

The large back-lit display makes it easy to select options and change/check reminders for filters, UV lamps and humidifier pads.

VisionPRO 8000 is compatible with RedLINK, which can add Internet and wireless capabilities to the thermostat.

Its everything you need to create a comfortable environment and save on energy while keeping convenience in mind.

About Honeywell

Honeywell's roots reach to 1885, when an inventor named Albert Butz patented the furnace regulator and alarm. He formed the Butz Thermo-Electric Regulator Co., Minneapolis, in April, 1886, and soon invented a device he called the "damper flapper an ingenious predecessor to the modern thermostat.

  • Robert Catlett
    5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
    Great for upstairs temperature inconsistencies
    Reviewed in the United States on March 11, 2018
    Style: Thermostat
    Wow! We have a 2-story house with a dual zoned HVAC system (2 thermostats to control upstairs and downstairs independently through adjustable dampers with only 1 air conditioner). We have had major problems with consistent air temps in the upstairs since we moved in. The... See more
    Wow! We have a 2-story house with a dual zoned HVAC system (2 thermostats to control upstairs and downstairs independently through adjustable dampers with only 1 air conditioner). We have had major problems with consistent air temps in the upstairs since we moved in. The 2 bedrooms in the front face the sun all day and have lots of large windows. Those rooms get HOT when it's sunny outside. The 2 bedrooms in the back are comfortable or even cool. The thermostat is located in the hallway right beside the stairwell, where all the hot air from downstairs rises. To make matters worse, it's feet away from the laundry room. We tried everything...spent $1000 to get the windows tinted in the front bedrooms, bought black-out curtains, had the air people come out and adjust our dampers multiple times and install some sort of blower for the room at the end of the run. Finally, we bought this thermostat with 4 sensors, 1 to go in each bedroom. We had our air people install it since we're still within our 1 year warranty, and they did it for free. This setup is amazing! We have it take the average of all the rooms, and now we get a very consistent temperature, even in the hallway. We stuck the sensors on the walls using medium command strips (the ones that are like Velcro), so it will be easy to pull off and change batteries when we need to. The thermostat is great because you can set a range of temperatures (minimum of 2 degrees apart), and it will automatically change from heat to air conditioner. Right now it's nearing spring, so it gets warm enough for the air conditioner during the day but cool enough for heat at night. I used to get up cold in the middle of the night and turn the heat on. Now, I set it for a range of 69-71. The air conditioner cools it if it gets above 71, but when it gets cooler at night and drops below 69, the heat kicks on. So amazing!!!
    Also, our HVAC guy recommended we buy the thermostat used. He said you'll be able to tell if it works or not instantly when you connect it, and Amazon's return policy is excellent, so it's worth the chance. We bought one in good condition on Amazon for $100 less than a brand new one, and the battery tab hadn't even been pulled out. Saved us a lot of money and hadn't ever been installed before!

    I'm updating my review in part of the product and in part due to the vendor. The first thermostat I got never worked correctly. Amazon refused to help as it was over 30 days when I contacted them. They referred me to Honeywell to make a warranty claim. Honeywell said I had no warranty as I had not had an authorized Honeywell installer put it in. There is nothing in the warranty info for this product which says anything about who installs it or length of warranty. Luckily, an Amazon rep had given me the contact info for the vendor. I contacted him and he went well out of his way to get me a working thermostat. The vendor, Ginko Magic, gets 5+ stars, Amazon and Honeywell get none. The thermostat, one that has all it's parts, works well. The app is simple and straightforward. If you have a need to control or check the heat/AC while away from home, it does the job. Please note, it does require it's own router which needs to be purchased separately. To get clarity from Honeywell, I will send a letter to their CEO to get their warranty position in writing.

    used for residential purposes with a Redlink remote temp sensor. Programming info was sparse and obscure- even for a technical person like me. I had to resort to YouTube videos to navigate thru the process. I could not find any useful documentation on the Honeywell site for a programming guide for this product with all its parameters. oddly, installation instructions were provided (in many languages) and Installation itself (how to mount it to a wall) was intuitive for almost any handy person even without the pages of multi-lingual instructions. Honeywell would be well advised to publish a step by step programming guide and perhaps a QR code which hyperlinks to the appropriate place on their website. The unit appears to work well (although still working thru fan control programming in the installer mode), but programming help is virtually absent from this product.
